x4freetext: Decay data given
Neutron Generator operated at a high
voltage of 120 KV and a beam current of 500 mu-A.
The neutron generator operated at a voltage of
120 KV and a deuteron beam current of 500 uA.
The samples were irradiated at zero degree relative to
the incoming deuteron beam.
The samples were sandwiched between Al foils, which
acted as a standard and flux monitors
98.6 cm3, resolution of 1.7 keV for the
1332 keV line of 60Co.
Irradiated for 10 min for Se and Mo,
15 min for Pt and Au, 20 min for In, 30 min for Br
and Zr.
Corrections have been made for
- dead time,
- coincidence sum effects of cascade gamma rays,
- pulse pile-up.
